# NPM Install Fix

The dependency conflict occurs because `react-helmet-async@2.0.5` hasn't been updated to officially support React 19 yet.

## Solution

Use the `--legacy-peer-deps` flag when installing:

```bash
npm install --legacy-peer-deps
```

## Alternative: Add to .npmrc

Create a `.npmrc` file in your project root with:

```
legacy-peer-deps=true
```

This will make all future `npm install` commands use legacy peer dependency resolution automatically.

## Why This Works

- `react-helmet-async` works fine with React 19 in practice
- The peer dependency constraint just hasn't been updated yet
- Using `--legacy-peer-deps` bypasses the strict version check
- All functionality remains intact (as proven by successful build)
